e=\"counter-reset: codeblock;\" class=\"tw-block tw-m-0 tw-p-0\"\u003e\u003ccode \r\n    id=\"codeblock-id-18\" \r\n    class=\"\r\n      chroma \r\n      !tw-block \r\n      tw-p-0\r\n      tw-m-0\r\n      tw-transition-[max-height] \r\n      tw-duration-500 \r\n      tw-ease-in-out \r\n      group-[.is-closed]:!tw-max-h-0 \r\n      group-[.is-wrap]:tw-text-wrap\r\n      tw-overflow-y-hidden\r\n      tw-overflow-x-auto\r\n      tw-scrollbar-thin\r\n      \"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"nx\"\u003eonSearchInput\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e(\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"nx\"\u003eevent\u003c/span\u003e: \u003cspan class=\"kt\"\u003eEvent\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e)\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"o\"\u003e:\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"k\"\u003evoid\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e{\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e  \u003cspan class=\"kr\"\u003econst\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"nx\"\u003evalue\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"o\"\u003e=\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e(\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"nx\"\u003eevent\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e.\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"nx\"\u003etarget\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"kr\"\u003eas\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"nx\"\u003eHTMLInputElement\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e).\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"nx\"\u003evalue\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e;\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e  \u003cspan class=\"k\"\u003ethis\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e.\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"nx\"\u003esearchQuery\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e.\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"kr\"\u003eset\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e(\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"nx\"\u003evalue\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e);\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"c1\"\u003e// This one line triggers everything\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"c1\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e}\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003esearchQuery\u003c/code\u003e updates → \u003ccode\u003eparams\u003c/code\u003e re-evaluates → old request aborted → new loader runs → \u003ccode\u003estatus\u003c/code\u003e and \u003ccode\u003evalue\u003c/code\u003e signals update → template re-renders.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eNo \u003ccode\u003edebounceTime\u003c/code\u003e. No \u003ccode\u003eswitchMap\u003c/code\u003e. No \u003ccode\u003etakeUntilDestroyed\u003c/code\u003e. Just Signals.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"coming-up-next\" class=\"headerLink\"\u003e\r\n    \u003ca href=\"#coming-up-next\" class=\"header-mark\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e6 Coming Up Next\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eWe\u0026rsquo;ve handled the data lifecycle and cancellation. But how does the UI \u003cem\u003elook\u003c/em\u003e during each phase? In \u003cstrong\u003ePhase 3B.3\u003c/strong\u003e, we\u0026rsquo;ll build a comprehensive status-driven UI that handles all six \u003ccode\u003eResourceStatus\u003c/code\u003e states.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eTry typing fast in the search box and watch the browser DevTools network tab. You\u0026rsquo;ll see cancelled requests — that\u0026rsquo;s \u003ccode\u003eabortSignal\u003c/code\u003e at work!\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e",
        "language": "en"
    },
    {
        "title" : "Angular Enterprise Dashboard - Phase 3B.1: Taming Async — Core resource() Mechanics",
        "date_published" : "2026-03-01T10:12:39+02:00",
        "date_modified" : "2026-03-01T10:53:36+02:00",
        "id" : "https://buffos.github.io/2026-03-18-phase-03b-part-01/",
        "url" : "https://buffos.github.io/2026-03-18-phase-03b-part-01/",
        "summary": "Welcome to Phase 3B — the deepest technical dive in our series so far. In Phase 3A, we pre-fetched data using resolvers. But resolvers are a routing tool. What about data that depends on user interaction — a search query, a filter, a date picker?\n",
        "content_html" : "\u003cp\u003eWelcome to Phase 3B — the deepest technical dive in our series so far. In Phase 3A, we pre-fetched data using resolvers. But resolvers are a \u003cem\u003erouting\u003c/em\u003e tool. What about data that depends on user interaction — a search query, a filter, a date picker?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch1 id=\"a-new-primitive-for-async-data\" class=\"headerLink\"\u003e\r\n    \u003ca href=\"#a-new-primitive-for-async-data\" class=\"header-mark\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003eA New Primitive for Async Data\u003c/h1\u003e\u003cp\u003eThis is where Angular\u0026rsquo;s \u003cstrong\u003e\u003ccode\u003eresource()\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e API enters the picture. It\u0026rsquo;s a low-level, framework-agnostic async primitive that gives you full control over the data lifecycle.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIn this first post, we\u0026rsquo;ll lay the groundwork: the data model, the API service, and the core \u003ccode\u003eresource()\u003c/code\u003e declaration.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"-what-is-resource\" class=\"headerLink\"\u003e\r\n    \u003ca href=\"#-what-is-resource\" class=\"header-mark\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e1 🧠 What is \u003ccode\u003eresource()\u003c/code\u003e?\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eThink of \u003ccode\u003eresource()\u003c/code\u003e as a \u003cstrong\u003ereactive async container\u003c/strong\u003e. You give it:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eA \u003cstrong\u003e\u003ccode\u003eparams\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e computation — a reactive expression that returns the request parameters.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eA \u003cstrong\u003e\u003ccode\u003eloader\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e function — an async function that fetches the data.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWhenever \u003ccode\u003eparams\u003c/code\u003e changes (because a signal it depends on changed), the resource automatically re-invokes the loader. It tracks status, exposes the value, and handles errors — all as Signals.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre class=\"mermaid\"\u003egraph LR\r\n    Signal[\"searchQuery signal\"] --\u003e Params[\"params() computation\"]\r\n    Params --\u003e Loader[\"loader({ params, abortSignal })\"]\r\n    Loader --\u003e Status[\"status signal\"]\r\n    Loader --\u003e Value[\"value signal\"]\r\n    Loader --\u003e Error[\"error signal\"]\r\n\u003c/pre\u003e\u003chr\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"-step-1-the-domain-model\" class=\"headerLink\"\u003e\r\n    \u003ca href=\"#-step-1-the-domain-model\" class=\"header-mark\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e2 🏗️ Step 1: The Domain Model\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eWe define a \u003ccode\u003eProject\u003c/code\u003e entity and a \u003ccode\u003eProjectSearchParams\u003c/code\u003e type:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"code-block highlight is-closed show-line-numbers  tw-group tw-my-2\"\u003e\r\n  \u003cdiv class=\"\r\n    \r\n    tw-flex \r\n    tw-flex-row\r\n    tw-flex-1 \r\n    tw-justify-between \r\n    tw-w-full tw-bg-bgColor-secondary\r\n    \"\u003e      \r\n    \u003cbutton \r\n      class=\"\r\n        code-block-button\r\n        tw-mx-2 \r\n        tw-flex\r\n        tw-flex-row\r\n        tw-flex-1\"\r\n      aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\r\n          \u003cdiv class=\"group-[.is-open]:tw-rotate-90 tw-transition-[transform] tw-duration-500 tw-ease-in-out print:!tw-hidden tw-w-min tw-h-min tw-my-1 tw-mx-1\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"icon\"\n    xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 320 512\"\u003e\u003c!-- Font Awesome Free 5.15.4 by @fontawesome - https://fontawesome.com License - https://fontawesome.com/license/free (Icons: CC BY 4.0, Fonts: SIL OFL 1.1, Code: MIT License) --\u003e\u003cpath d=\"M285.476 272.971L91.132 467.314c-9.373 9.373-24.569 9.373-33.941 0l-22.667-22.667c-9.357-9.357-9.375-24.522-.04-33.901L188.505 256 34.484 101.255c-9.335-9.379-9.317-24.544.04-33.901l22.667-22.667c9.373-9.373 24.569-9.373 33.941 0L285.475 239.03c9.373 9.372 9.373 24.568.001 33.941z\"/\u003e\u003c/svg\u0