me - https://fontawesome.com License - https://fontawesome.com/license/free (Icons: CC BY 4.0, Fonts: SIL OFL 1.1, Code: MIT License) --\u003e\u003cpath d=\"M328 256c0 39.8-32.2 72-72 72s-72-32.2-72-72 32.2-72 72-72 72 32.2 72 72zm104-72c-39.8 0-72 32.2-72 72s32.2 72 72 72 72-32.2 72-72-32.2-72-72-72zm-352 0c-39.8 0-72 32.2-72 72s32.2 72 72 72 72-32.2 72-72-32.2-72-72-72z\"/\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c/button\u003e\r\n    \u003c/div\u003e\r\n  \u003c/div\u003e\r\n  \u003cpre style=\"counter-reset: codeblock;\" class=\"tw-block tw-m-0 tw-p-0\"\u003e\u003ccode \r\n    id=\"codeblock-id-12\" \r\n    class=\"\r\n      chroma \r\n      !tw-block \r\n      tw-p-0\r\n      tw-m-0\r\n      tw-transition-[max-height] \r\n      tw-duration-500 \r\n      tw-ease-in-out \r\n      group-[.is-closed]:!tw-max-h-0 \r\n      group-[.is-wrap]:tw-text-wrap\r\n      tw-overflow-y-hidden\r\n      tw-overflow-x-auto\r\n      tw-scrollbar-thin\r\n      \"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"nx\"\u003ehasRole\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e(\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"nx\"\u003erole\u003c/span\u003e: \u003cspan class=\"kt\"\u003eUserRole\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"o\"\u003e|\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"nx\"\u003eUserRole\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e[])\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"o\"\u003e:\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"kr\"\u003eboolean\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e{\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e  \u003cspan class=\"kr\"\u003econst\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"nx\"\u003euserRole\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"o\"\u003e=\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"k\"\u003ethis\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e.\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"nx\"\u003euserRole\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e();\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e  \u003cspan class=\"k\"\u003eif\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e(\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"nb\"\u003eArray\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e.\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"nx\"\u003eisArray\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e(\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"nx\"\u003erole\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e))\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e{\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e    \u003cspan class=\"k\"\u003ereturn\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"nx\"\u003erole\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e.\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"nx\"\u003eincludes\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e(\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"nx\"\u003euserRole\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e);\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e  \u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e}\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e  \u003cspan class=\"k\"\u003ereturn\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"nx\"\u003euserRole\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"o\"\u003e===\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"nx\"\u003erole\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e;\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e}\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003ch2 id=\"coming-up-next\" class=\"headerLink\"\u003e\r\n    \u003ca href=\"#coming-up-next\" class=\"header-mark\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e5 Coming Up Next\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eManaging state is only half the battle. How do we ensure users can\u0026rsquo;t navigate to parts of the app they shouldn\u0026rsquo;t see?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIn our next post, we\u0026rsquo;ll dive into \u003cstrong\u003ePhase 2.2: Functional Route Guards\u003c/strong\u003e, where we\u0026rsquo;ll see these Signals in action protecting our application\u0026rsquo;s perimeter.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eFound this useful? Every line of this dashboard is designed to be production-ready. Check out the full source code on GitHub!\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e",
        "language": "en"
    },
    {
        "title" : "Angular Enterprise Dashboard - Phase 1: Building a Resilient Core with Dependency Injection",
        "date_published" : "2026-02-15T14:52:37+02:00",
        "date_modified" : "2026-02-16T22:47:53+02:00",
        "id" : "https://buffos.github.io/2026-03-15-angular-enterprise-board-part-02/",
        "url" : "https://buffos.github.io/2026-03-15-angular-enterprise-board-part-02/",
        "summary": "Welcome to the second post in our series. In the Introduction, we talked about the vision. Now, it\u0026rsquo;s time to get our hands dirty. Phase 1 was all about the foundation—the invisible plumbing that makes a professional application robust or brittle.\n",
        "content_html" : "\u003cp\u003eWelcome to the second post in our series. In the \u003ca href=\"/blog/introduction\" rel=\"\"\u003eIntroduction\u003c/a\u003e, we talked about the vision. Now, it\u0026rsquo;s time to get our hands dirty. \u003cstrong\u003ePhase 1\u003c/strong\u003e was all about the foundation—the invisible plumbing that makes a professional application robust or brittle.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch1 id=\"the-foundation-why-architecture-matters\" class=\"headerLink\"\u003e\r\n    \u003ca href=\"#the-foundation-why-architecture-matters\" class=\"header-mark\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003eThe Foundation: Why Architecture Matters\u003c/h1\u003e\u003cp\u003eToday, we\u0026rsquo;re dissecting the core architecture of our dashboard, focusing on one of Angular\u0026rsquo;s most powerful (and often misunderstood) tools: \u003cstrong\u003eDependency Injection (DI)\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"-going-zoneless\" class=\"headerLink\"\u003e\r\n    \u003ca href=\"#-going-zoneless\" class=\"header-mark\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e1 🚀 Going Zoneless\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eBefore we dive into DI, let\u0026rsquo;s talk about performance. Our first major architectural decision was to go \u003cstrong\u003eZoneless\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIn traditional Angular, \u003ccode\u003eZone.js\u003c/code\u003e monkey-patches the browser to detect when \u0026ldquo;something happened\u0026rdquo; and triggers change detection. In this project, we explicitly opt-out:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"code-block highlight is-open show-line-numbers  tw-group tw-my-2\"\u003e\r\n  \u003cdiv class=\"\r\n    \r\n    tw-flex \r\n    tw-flex-row\r\n    tw-flex-1 \r\n    tw-justify-between \r\n    tw-w-full tw-bg-bgColor-secondary\r\n    \"\u003e      \r\n    \u003cbutton \r\n      class=\"\r\n        code-block-button\r\n        tw-mx-2 \r\n        tw-flex\r\n        tw-flex-row\r\n        tw-flex-1\"\r\n      aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\r\n          \u003cdiv class=\"group-[.is-open]:tw-rotate-90 tw-transition-[transform] tw-duration-500 tw-ease-in-out print:!tw-hidden tw-w-min tw-h-min tw-my-1 tw-mx-1\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"icon\"\n    xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 320 512\"\u003e\u003c!-- Font Awesome Free 5.15.4 by @fontawesome - https://fontawesome.com License - https://fontawesome.com/license/free (Icons: CC BY 4.0, Fonts: SIL OFL 1.1, Code: MIT License) --\u003e\u003cpath d=\"M285.476 272.971L91.132 467.314c-9.373 9.373-24.569 9.373-33.941 0l-22.667-22.667c-9.357-9.357-9.375-24.522-.04-33.901L188.505 256 34.484 101.255c-9.335-9.379-9.317-24.544.04-33.901l22.667-22.667c9.373-9.373 24.569-9.373 33.941 0L285.475 239.03c9.373 9.372 9.373 24.568.001 33.941z\"/\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\r\n          \u003cp class=\"tw-select-none !tw-my-1\"\u003etypescript\u003c/p\u003e\r\n      \u003c/button\u003e\r\n\r\n   \u003cdiv class=\"tw-flex\"\u003e\r\n      \u003cbutton \r\n        class=\"\r\n          line-number-button\r\n          tw-mx-2 \r\n          tw-hidden \r\n          group-[.is-open]:tw-block \r\n          group-[.show-line-numbers]:tw-text-fgColor-link \r\n          print:!tw-hidden\" \r\n        title=\"Toggle line numbers\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"icon\"\n    xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 512 512\"\u003e\u003c!-- Font Awesome Free 5.15.4 by @fontawesome - https://fontawesome.com License - https://fontawesome.com/license/free (Icons: CC BY 4.0, Fonts: SIL OFL 1.1, Code: MIT License) --\u003e\u003cpath d=\"M61.77 401l17.5-20.15a19.92 19.92 0 0 0 5.07-14.19v-3.31C84.34 356 80.5 352 73 352H16a8 8 0 0 0-8 8v16a8 8 0 0 0 8 8h22.83a157.41 157.41 0 0 0-11 12.31l-5.61 7c-4 5.07-5.25 10.13-2.8 14.88l1.05 1.93c3 5.76 6.29 7.88 12.25 7.88h4.73c10.33 0 15.94 2.44 15.94 9.09 0 4.72-4.2 8.22-14.36 8.22a41.54 41.54 0 0 1-15.47-3.12c-6.49-3.88-11.74-3.5-15.6 3.12l-5.59 9.31c-3.72 6.13-3.19 11.72 2.63 15.94 7.71 4.69 20.38 9.44 37 9.44 34.16 0 48.5-22.75 48.5-44.12-.03-14.38-9.12-29.76-28.73-34.88zM496 224H176a16 16 0 0 0-16 16v32a16 16 0 0 0 16 16h320a16 16 0 0 0 16-16v-32a16 16 0 0 0-16-16zm0-160H176a16 16 0 0 0-16 16v32a16 16 0 0 0 16 16h320a16 16 0 0 0 16-16V80a16 16 0 0 0-16-16zm0 320H176a16 16 0 0 0-16 16v32a16 16 0 0 0 16 16h320a16 16 0 0 0 16-16v-32a16 16 0 0 0-16-16zM16 160h64a8 8 0 0 0 8-8v-16a8 8 0 0 0-8-8H64V40a8 8 0 0 0-8-8H32a8 8 0 0 0-7.14 4.42l-8 16A8 8 0 0 0 24 64h8v64H16a8 8 0 0 0-8 8v16a8 8 0 0 0 8 8zm-3.91 160H80a8 8 0 0 0 8-8v-16a8 8 0 0 0-8-8H41.32c3.29-10.29 48.34-18.68 48.34-56.44 0-29.06-25-39.56-44.47-39.56-21.36 0-33.8 10-40.46 18.75-4.37 5.59-3 10.84 2.8 15.37l8.58 6.88c5.61 4.56 11 2.47 16.12-2.44a13.44 13.44 0 0 1 9.46-3.84c3.33 0 9.28 1.56 9.28 8.75C51 248.19 0 257.31 0 304.59v4C0 316 5.08 320 12.09 320z\"/\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c/button\u003e\r\n\r\n      \u003cbutton \r\n        class=\"\r\n          wrap-code-button\r\n          tw-select-none \r\n          tw-mx-2 \r\n          tw-hidden \r\n          group-[.is-open]:tw-block \r\n          group-[.is-wrap]:tw-text-fgColor-link \r\n          print:!tw-hidden\" \r\n        title=\"Toggle code wrap\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"icon\"\n    xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 448 512\"\u003e\u003c!-- Font Awesome Free 5.15.4 by @fontawesome - https://fontawesome.com License - https://fontawesome.com/license/free (Icons: CC BY 4.0, Fonts: SIL OFL 1.1, Code: MIT License) --\u003e\u003cpath d=\"M16 132h416c8.837 0 16-7.163 16-16V76c0-8.837-7.163-16-16-16H16C7.163 60 0 67.163 0 76v40c0 8.837 7.163 16 16 16zm0 160h416c8.837 0 16-7.163 16-16v-40c0-8.837-7.163-16-16-16H16c-8.837 0-16 7.163-16 16v40c0 8.837 7.163 16 16 16zm0 160h416c8.837 0 16-7.163 16-16v-40c0-8.837-7.163-16-16-16H16c-8.837 0-16 7.163-16 16v40c0 8.837 7.163 16 16 16z\"/\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c/button\u003e\r\n      \r\n      \u003cbutton \r\n        class=\"\r\n          copy-code-button\r\n          tw-select-none\r\n          tw-mx-2 \r\n          tw-hidden\r\n          group-[.is-open]:tw-block\r\n          hover:tw-text-fgColor-link \r\n          print:!tw-hidden\"\r\n        title=\"Copy code\"\u003e\r\n          \u003cspan class=\"copy-icon tw-block\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"icon\"\n    xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 448 512\"\u003e\u003c!-- Font Awesome Free 5.15.4 by @fontawesome - https://fontawesome.com License - https://fontawesome.com/license/free (Icons: CC BY 4.0, Fonts: SIL OFL 1.1, Code: MIT License) --\u003e\u003cpath d=\"M433.941 65.941l-51.882-51.882A48 48 0 0 0 348.118 0H176c-26.51 0-48 21.49-48 48v48H48c-26.51 0-48 21.49-48 48v320c0 26.51 21.49 48 48 48h224c26.51 0 48-21.49 48-48v-48h80c26.51 0 48-21.49 48-48V99.882a48 48 0 0 0-14.059-33.941zM266 464H54a6 6 0 0 1-6-6V150a6 6 0 0 1 6-6h74v224c0 26.51 21.49 48 48 48h96v42a6 6 0 0 1-6 6zm128-96H182a6 6 0 0 1-6-6V54a6 6 0 0 1 6-6h106v88c0 13.255 10.745 24 24 24h88v202a6 6 0 0 1-6 6zm6-256h-64V48h9.632c1.591 0 3.117.632 4.243 1.757l48.368 48.368a6 6 0 0 1 1.757 4.243V112z\"/\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\r\n          \u003cspan class=\"check-icon tw-hidden\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"icon\"\n    xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 512 512\"\u003e\u003c!-- Font Awesome Free 5.15.4 by @fontawesome - https://fontawesome.com License - https://fontawesome.com/license/free (Icons: CC BY 4.0, Fonts: SIL OFL 1.1, Code: MIT License) --\u003e\u003cpath d=\"M173.898 439.404l-166.4-166.4c-9.997-9.997-9.997-26.206 0-36.204l36.203-36.204c9.997-9.998 26.207-9.998 36.204 0L192 312.69 432.095 72.596c9.997-9.997 26.207-9.997 36.204 0l36.203 36.204c9.997 9.997 9.997 26.206 0 36.204l-294.4 294.401c-9.998 9.997-26.207 9.997-36.204-.001z\"/\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\r\n      \u003c/button\u003e\r\n        \r\n      \u003cbutton \r\n        class=\"\r\n          tw-select-none \r\n          tw-mx-2 \r\n          tw-block \r\n          group-[.is-open]:tw-hidden \r\n          print:!tw-hidden\" \r\n        disabled\r\n        aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"icon\"\n    xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 512 512\"\u003e\u003c!-- Font Awesome Free 5.15.4 by @fontawesome - https://fontawesome.com License - https://fontawesome.com/license/free (Icons: CC BY 4.0, Fonts: SIL OFL 1.1, Code: MIT License) --\u003e\u003cpath d=\"M328 256c0 39.8-32.2 72-72 72s-72-32.2-72-72 32.2-72 72-72 72 32.2 72 72zm104-72c-39.8 0-72 32.2-72 72s32.2 72 72 72 72-32.2 72-72-32.2-72-72-72zm-352 0c-39.8 0-72 32.2-72 72s32.2 72 72 72 72-32.2 72-72-32.2-72-72-72z\"/\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c/button\u003e\r\n    \u003c/div\u003e\r\n  \u003c/div\u003e\r\n  \u003cpre style=\"counter-reset: codeblock;\" class=\"tw-block tw-m-0 tw-p-0\"\u003e\u003ccode \r\n    id=\"codeblock-id-11\" \r\n    class=\"\r\n      chroma \r\n      !tw-block \r\n      tw-p-0\r\n      tw-m-0\r\n      tw-transition-[max-height] \r\n      tw-duration-500 \r\n      tw-ease-in-out \r\n      group-[.is-closed]:!tw-max-h-0 \r\n      group-[.is-wrap]:tw-text-wrap\r\n      tw-overflow-y-hidden\r\n      tw-overflow-x-auto\r\n      tw-scrollbar-thin\r\n      \"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"c1\"\u003e// app.config.ts\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"c1\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"kr\"\u003eexport\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"kr\"\u003econst\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"nx\"\u003eappConfig\u003c/span\u003e: \u003cspan class=\"kt\"\u003eApplicationConfig\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"o\"\u003e=\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e{\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e  \u003cspan class=\"nx\"\u003eproviders\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"o\"\u003e:\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e[\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e    \u003cspan class=\"nx\"\u003eprovideZonelessChangeDetection\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e(),\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e    \u003cspan class=\"c1\"\u003e// ...\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"c1\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e  \u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e],\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e};\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Teaching Moment:\u003c/strong\u003e Why? Eliminating Zone.js reduces initial bundle size and makes change detection more predictable and performant. It forces us to use \u003cstrong\u003eSignals\u003c/strong\u003e, ensuring that only the parts of the DOM that actually need updating are touched.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"-the-power-of-injectiontokens\" class=\"headerLink\"\u003e\r\n    \u003ca href=\"#-the-power-of-injectiontokens\" class=\"header-mark\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e2 🛠️ The Power of InjectionTokens\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eIn many apps, you might see configuration passed around like this:\n\u003ccode\u003econst API_URL = 'http://localhost:3000';\u003c/code\u003e (Brittle! Hard to test!)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIn an enterprise setting, we treat configuration as a \u003cstrong\u003edependency\u003c/strong\u003e. This is where \u003ccode\u003eInjectionToken\u003c/code\u003e shines.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"what-problem-does-it-solve\" class=\"headerLink\"\u003e\r\n    \u003ca href=\"#what-problem-does-it-solve\" class=\"header-mark\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e2.1 What problem does it solve?\u003c/h3\u003e\u003cp\u003eImagine you have multiple services that need the same API configuration. If you import a constant, you\u0026rsquo;ve created a hard dependency. You can\u0026rsquo;t easily swap that constant for a different value during unit tests or for different environments without modifying the code itself.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBy using an \u003ccode\u003eInjectionToken\u003c/code\u003e, we decouple the \u003cem\u003eneed\u003c/em\u003e for a value from the \u003cem\u003evalue itself\u003c/em\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre class=\"mermaid\"\u003egraph TD\r\n    subgraph \"The DI Container\"\r\n        Token[\"APP_CONFIG Token\"]\r\n        Val[\"{ apiUrl: '...', production: true }\"]\r\n        Provider[\"{ provide: Token, useValue: Val }\"]\r\n    end\r\n\r\n    subgraph \"Consumers\"\r\n        ServiceA[\"AnalyticsService\"]\r\n        ServiceB[\"AuthService\"]\r\n    end\r\n\r\n    Token --\u003e Provider\r\n    Provider -.-\u003e ServiceA\r\n    Provider -.-\u003e ServiceB\r\n\u003c/pre\u003e\u003ch3 id=\"implementation-in-the-wild\" class=\"headerLink\"\u003e\r\n    \u003ca href=\"#implementation-in-the-wild\" class=\"header-mark\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e2.2 Implementation in the Wild\u003c/h3\u003e\u003cp\u003eIn our project, we define our tokens in \u003ccode\u003ecore/tokens/app-config.token.ts\u003c/code\u003e:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"code-block highlight is-open show-line-numbers  tw-group tw-my-2\"\u003e\r\n  \u003cdiv class=\"\r\n    \r\n    tw-flex \r\n    tw-flex-row\r\n    tw-flex-1 \r\n    tw-justify-between \r\n    tw-w-full tw-bg-bgColor-secondary\r\n    \"\u003e      \r\n    \u003cbutton \r\n      class=\"\r\n        code-block-button\r\n        tw-mx-2 \r\n        tw-flex\r\n        tw-flex-row\r\n        tw-flex-1\"\r\n      aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\r\n          \u003cdiv class=\"group-[.is-open]:tw-rotate-90 tw-transition-[transform] tw-duration-500 tw-ease-in-out print:!tw-hidden tw-w-min tw-h-min tw-my-1 tw-mx-1\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"icon\"\n    xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 320 512\"\u003e\u003c!-- Font Awesome Free 5.15.4 by @fontawesome - https://fontawesome.com License - https://fontawesome.com/license/free (Icons: CC BY 4.0, Fonts: SIL OFL 1.1, Code: MIT License) --\u003e\u003cpath d=\"M285.476 272.971L91.132 467.314c-9.373 9.373-24.569 9.373-33.941 0l-22.667-22.667c-9.357-9.357-9.375-24.522-.04-33.901L188.505 256 34.484 101.255c-9.335-9.379-9.317-24.544.04-33.901l22.667-22.667c9.373-9.373 24.569-9.373 33.941 0L285.475 239.03c9.373 9.372 9.373 24.568.001 33.941z\"/\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\r\n          \u003cp class=\"tw-select-none !tw-my-1\"\u003etypescript\u003c/p\u003e\r\n      \u003c/button\u003e\r\n\r\n   \u003cdiv class=\"tw-flex\"\u003e\r\n      \u003cbutton \r\n        class=\"\r\n          line-number-button\r\n          tw-mx-2 \r\n          tw-hidden \r\n          group-[.is-open]:tw-block \r\n          group-[.show-line-numbers]:tw-text-fgColor-link \r\n          print:!tw-hidden\" \r\n        title=\"Toggle line numbers\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"icon\"\n    xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 512 512\"\u003e\u003c!-- Font Awesome Free 5.15.4 by @fontawesome - https://fontawesome.com License - https://fontawesome.com/license/free (Icons: CC BY 4.0, Fonts: SIL OFL 1.1, Code: MIT License) --\u003e\u003cpath d=\"M61.77 401l17.5-20.15a19.92 19.92 0 0 0 5.07-14.19v-3.31C84.34 356 80.5 352 73 352H16a8 8 0 0 0-8 8v16a8 8 0 0 0 8 8h22.83a157.41 157.41 0 0 0-11 12.31l-5.61 7c-4 5.07-5.25 10.13-2.8 14.88l1.05 1.93c3 5.76 6.29 7.88 12.25 7.88h4.73c10.33 0 15.94 2.44 15.94 9.09 0 4.72-4.2 8.22-14.36 8.22a41.54 41.54 0 0 1-15.47-3.12c-6.49-3.88-11.74-3.5-15.6 3.12l-5.59 9.31c-3.72 6.13-3.19 11.72 2.63 15.94 7.71 4.69 20.38 9.44 37 9.44 34.16 0 48.5-22.75 48.5-44.12-.03-14.38-9.12-29.76-28.73-34.88zM496 224H176a16 16 0 0 0-16 16v32a16 16 0 0 0 16 16h320a16 16 0 0 0 16-16v-32a16 16 0 0 0-16-16zm0-160H176a16 16 0 0 0-16 16v32a16 16 0 0 0 16 16h320a16 16 0 0 0 16-16V80a16 16 0 0 0-16-16zm0 320H176a16 